## Stack: .NET 9 + ASP.NET Core MVC + EF Core 9

| Layer | Tech |
|---|---|
| Framework | ASP.NET Core MVC 9 |
| Language | C# 13 (nullable reference types enabled) |
| ORM | EF Core 9 (Pomelo.EntityFrameworkCore.MySql or Npgsql.EntityFrameworkCore.PostgreSQL) |
| DI | Built-in `IServiceCollection` (no third-party container) |
| Logging | `Microsoft.Extensions.Logging` (Serilog optional sink) |
| Testing | xUnit + FluentAssertions + `WebApplicationFactory<TEntryPoint>` |
| Migrations | `dotnet ef migrations` |
| Build | `dotnet build` / `dotnet test` / `dotnet ef database update` |

### Conventions

- **Async all the way.** Every I/O path (DB, HTTP, file) is `async`/`await`. No `.Result`, `.Wait()`, or `.GetAwaiter().GetResult()` in application code.
- **`[Required]` over throw.** Validate inputs with data annotations / FluentValidation on ViewModels; let the framework return 400 rather than throwing inside actions.
- **Primary-constructor DI.** Inject dependencies through the controller / service primary constructor (`public class FooController(IFooService svc) : Controller`) — no field/property injection.
- **No static `DbContext`.** `DbContext` is scoped; never cache it in a static field or use it across requests.
- **Integration tests via `WebApplicationFactory`.** Spin up the real pipeline against an in-memory or test DB; xUnit + FluentAssertions for the assertions.
- **Nullable warnings are errors.** Don't suppress with `!` or `#pragma warning disable nullable` — fix the type.
- **Type-check before declaring done:** `dotnet build` (warnings-as-errors) and `dotnet test` must both pass.

### Common commands

```bash
dotnet restore
dotnet build                              # build + nullable + analyzer check
dotnet run --project src/Web              # dev server
dotnet test                               # xUnit suite
dotnet format --verify-no-changes         # style gate
dotnet ef migrations add <Name> -p src/Data -s src/Web
dotnet ef database update -p src/Data -s src/Web
```
